<p>Right now the <code>MessageHandler.Whole&lt;byte[]&gt;</code> only activates when the message is actually just bytes.</p>  <p><strong>Will only activate when bytes arrive</strong></p>  <pre><code>@Override public void onMessage(byte[] message) { ... } </code></pre>  <p>Is it possible to get the raw message (the WebSocket should not check wether it is a string or not) even though it is actually text data? The reason for that is because it would give some performance benefit when parsing raw bytes instead of strings.</p>